# Methodology

The project began with a review of widely used short-term trading indicators to determine which tools were most commonly trusted by active traders and technical analysts.

From that initial research, indicators were evaluated for how well they behaved across a focused set of assets including leveraged ETFs, commodities, metals, volatility-related products, and selected crypto-linked instruments.

The final framework moved away from single-indicator dependence and toward a multi-factor model emphasizing:

- momentum exhaustion
- reversal confirmation
- volume support
- higher-timeframe exit logic

The objective was to improve signal quality and reduce false positives for short-term options-oriented decision-making.
